The paper deals with deep learning for 3D data and specifically addresses the issue of class imbalance in point clouds. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves augmentation techniques to address the class imbalance, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and graphics (cs.GR) research. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach using benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in natural language processing (cs.CL) and other sub-fields of computer science.
